==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Linguist
<hw>Lin"guist</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧⟦nsm⟧"gw⟦icr⟧st)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>lingua</ets> tongue, speech, language: cf. F.
<ets>linguiste</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A master of the use of
language; a talker.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I'll dispute with him;⟦br⟧
He's a rare <qex>linguist</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>J. Webster.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person skilled in languages.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There too were Gibbon, the greatest historian, and Jones, the
greatest <qex>linguist</qex>, of the age.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Linguistical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Linguistic</ent>⟦br⟧
